\begin_layout Standard
Main goal of steganography is to prevent embedding from being detected.
 A branch of steganography that develops ways of attacking embedding schemes
 is called steganalysis.
 Another deliverable of this project is to provide a toolkit to perform
 video steganalysis, that would neatly integrate with existing scientific
 computing packages (Matlab, Python-based libraries).
 One popular approach in steganalysis is to look at statistical differences
 of modified and unmodified values, as selectively modifying certain values
 may make them stand out from the rest.
 General approaches use histograms, Chi-Squared attacks and ones, specifically
 targeting motion vectors (Deng et al.), exploit correlations seen in neighbourho
ods of MVs and other statistical metrics.
 
\end_layout

