\begin_layout Section*
Extensions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Deng et al.
 propose to use various statistical differences between videos with and
 without embedded messages as features for a classifier.
 Using this, and other features proposed in similar works, goals of the
 project can be stretched to accommodate a classifier trained using machine
 learning.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Currently social networks, like YouTube, Facebook and Tumblr transcode (convert
 between formats) user-uploaded videos before presenting them to other users.
 This results in MVs being recomputed and overwritten, and hence the secret
 message is lost.
 This extension would explore more aggressive embedding, possibly using
 some control data and error-correction codes, to withstand such transcoding.
 
\end_layout

